<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1409,1614]" pageId="7" pageNumber="106">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1585880166" collectingDate="2003-05-28" country="Algeria, Morocco" county="Reserva Natural Especial Dunas de Maspalomas" location="North Africa" municipality="This" pageId="7" pageNumber="106" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Canary Islands">
Specimens of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Newstead" baseAuthorityYear="1895" box="[313,392,1410,1433]" class="Insecta" family="Diaspididae" genus="Voraspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nerii">
<emphasis box="[313,392,1410,1433]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="106">V. nerii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were collected from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Balachowsky" baseAuthorityYear="1954" box="[641,833,1409,1434]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Nerium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="7" pageNumber="106" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="oleander">
<emphasis box="[641,833,1409,1434]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="106">Nerium oleander</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. (
<taxonomicName authorityName="de Jussieu" authorityYear="1789" box="[883,1037,1410,1434]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="7" pageNumber="106" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Apocynaceae</taxonomicName>
) in Gran Canaria, 
<collectingCounty pageId="7" pageNumber="106">Reserva Natural Especial Dunas de Maspalomas</collectingCounty>
, on 
<collectingDate box="[585,757,1446,1470]" pageId="7" pageNumber="106" value="2003-05-28">
<date box="[585,757,1446,1470]" pageId="7" pageNumber="106" value="2003-05-28">May 28, 2003</date>
</collectingDate>
. 
<collectingMunicipality box="[773,823,1445,1470]" pageId="7" pageNumber="106">This</collectingMunicipality>
species was known only in 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:EB7C87D25B0AFFE6FF57FA8531D2F9CA:660A601F5B0AFFE6FB55FA19361DFA3A" box="[1173,1322,1445,1470]" country="Algeria, Morocco" county="Reserva Natural Especial Dunas de Maspalomas" municipality="This" name="North Africa" pageId="7" pageNumber="106" stateProvince="Canary Islands">North Africa</location>
(
<collectingCountry isEnumeration="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="106">Algeria, Morocco</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[266,354,1481,1506]" name="Tunisia" pageId="7" pageNumber="106">Tunisia</collectingCountry>
), penetrating along the wadis into 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:EB7C87D25B0AFFE6FF57FA8531D2F9CA:660A601F5B0AFFE6FD24FA7530BAFA66" box="[740,909,1481,1506]" country="Algeria, Morocco" county="Reserva Natural Especial Dunas de Maspalomas" municipality="This" name="Central Sahara" pageId="7" pageNumber="106" stateProvince="Canary Islands">Central Sahara</location>
, following the distribution of its host plant, the wild 
<taxonomicName authority="(Balachowsky 1954)" authorityName="Balachowsky" authorityYear="1954" baseAuthorityName="Balachowsky" baseAuthorityYear="1954" box="[208,584,1517,1542]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Nerium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="7" pageNumber="106" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="oleander">
<emphasis box="[208,341,1517,1542]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="106">N. oleander</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Balachowsky" box="[355,576,1517,1542]" pageId="7" pageNumber="106" refString="Balachowsky, A. S. (1954) Les cochenilles Palearctiques de la tribu des Diaspidini. Memoires Scientifiques de l'Institut Pasteur, Paris, 450 pp." type="book" year="1954">Balachowsky 1954</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:EB7C87D25B0AFFE6FF57FA8531D2F9CA:660A601F5B0AFFE6FD93FA513148F982" box="[595,639,1517,1542]" country="Algeria, Morocco" county="Reserva Natural Especial Dunas de Maspalomas" municipality="This" name="The" pageId="7" pageNumber="106" stateProvince="Canary Islands">The</location>
finding of this interesting autochthonous species in the 
<collectingRegion box="[1268,1436,1517,1542]" country="Spain" name="Canarias" pageId="7" pageNumber="106">Canary Islands</collectingRegion>
expands its known distributional range and confirms the hypothesis by 
<bibRefCitation author="Balachowsky" box="[965,1199,1553,1578]" pageId="7" pageNumber="106" refString="Balachowsky, A. S. (1946) Etude biogeographique des Coccoidea des Iles Atlantides (Canaries et Madere). Memoires de la Societe Biogeographique, 8, 209 - 218." type="journal article" year="1946">
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:EB7C87D25B0AFFE6FF57FA8531D2F9CA:660A601F5B0AFFE6FC05F9AD376BF9AE" box="[965,1116,1553,1578]" country="Algeria, Morocco" county="Reserva Natural Especial Dunas de Maspalomas" municipality="This" name="Balachowsky" pageId="7" pageNumber="106" stateProvince="Canary Islands">Balachowsky</location>
(1946)
</bibRefCitation>
on the affinity of its autochthonous scale insect fauna with that of Africa.
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
